Comment: 0,0:03:30.06,0:03:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Comment: 10,0:09:43.29,0:09:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Comment: 0,0:11:14.52,0:11:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Comment: 0,0:22:26.28,0:22:26.32,Song,,0,0,0,,{ED}
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:08.64,0:00:10.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,One evening,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.26,0:00:15.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as I returned to my room\N in Monbijoustrasse,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:15.02,0:00:17.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,while passing by Klosterstrasse, {the tled book I have goes "One evening I sauntered through the Tiergarten and then walked down Unter den Linden. On the way back to my lodgings in Monbijoustrasse, I came in front of the old church in Klosterstrasse. }
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.24,0:00:25.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I noticed a young girl sobbing\N near the closed door of the church.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:35.76,0:00:37.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,In 1884, {the 17th year of Meiji, }
Dialogue: 10,0:00:37.94,0:00:42.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,a certain government office \Nsent me to study in Germany.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:43.69,0:00:45.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,My destination was Berlin.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:46.00,0:00:49.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was assigned to the office there.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:50.28,0:00:53.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,But this time, my trip to Europe was more than sightseeing.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:53.83,0:00:57.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was to live there for several years,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:57.35,0:00:59.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,working with senior officials. {this novel is older than the others and the language is too archaic, I don't understand a thing tbh >_>}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:00.42,0:01:01.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was burning with ambition.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:03.63,0:01:08.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,My life began in the good old \Ncapital city of Berlin,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:08.36,0:01:10.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,where Wilhelm I still reigned.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:11.73,0:01:17.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, at my parents' urging,\N I had studied German and French as a child.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.23,0:01:21.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,I found work quickly after graduation.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:21.51,0:01:25.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,There were plenty of opportunities for a skilled interpreter.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:27.45,0:01:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.07,0:01:34.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,That winter,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.07,0:01:39.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,something happened \Nthat changed my life forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.65,0:01:42.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,That was the year I met Elise.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.75,0:02:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I help you, Fraulein?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.63,0:02:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so forlorn. I felt I had to ask.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.05,0:02:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you can tell me your problems.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.45,0:02:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. You don't need\N to be afraid of me.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.50,0:02:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I live on Monbijoustrasse. \NMy name is Ota Toyotaro.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.78,0:02:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be happy to help you if I can.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.72,0:02:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't cry. People are staring.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.74,0:02:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you live? I'll walk you home.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.78,0:02:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help me. My mother threw me out of the house.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.64,0:02:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She kept beating me.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.65,0:02:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My father's dead.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.30,0:02:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to hold his funeral tomorrow,\Nbut we have no money!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.08,0:02:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. \NCome on, I'll take you home.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.20,0:03:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.64,0:03:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Elise.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.88,0:03:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you been?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.90,0:03:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been gone \Nfor more than an hour! Come in!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.34,0:03:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't even buried your father yet, \Nand you're wandering off somewhere! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.85,0:03:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.56,0:03:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Mein Herr. \NI didn't mean to be rude.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.29,0:03:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Our place may be a rather decrepit, \Nbut please come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.68,0:03:48.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,The mother told me that her husband \Nhad worked as a tailor, a good one.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.02,0:03:50.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,He had just passed away, \Nafter a prolonged struggle.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.75,0:03:52.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,As a result, the family's finances
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.23,0:03:57.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,had deteriorated to the point where they didn't know if they'd eat tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.35,0:04:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother wanted me to go\N to the moneylender living nearby.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:08.00,0:04:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Moneylender?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.59,0:04:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a nasty character. We've already borrowed money from him before.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:15.48,0:04:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time he wanted me as collateral!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.77,0:04:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He was really persistent too.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.93,0:04:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather die than go live \Nwith a man like him!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.22,0:04:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's an outrageous request, \Nbut could you lend us some money?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.83,0:04:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pay you back every month \Nfrom my salary.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.99,0:04:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we won't bother you ever again!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.42,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a job?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.87,0:04:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know the Victoria Theater? {can't find it on gmaps}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.76,0:04:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they often stage ballets there.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.29,0:04:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm one of their dancers.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.47,0:04:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I only have two or three marks \Nin cash at present.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.28,0:04:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It would obviously not be enough, \Nso I'd like you to have this.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.91,0:05:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the pawnbroker's man if he calls on Ota at 3 Monbijoustrasse,{meaning "Monbijoustrasse house 3"}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.00,0:05:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll redeem it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.90,0:05:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget your kindness.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.45,0:05:31.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,And so, from that day onward,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.57,0:05:35.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,my relationship with Elise deepened day by day.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.83,0:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for waiting.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.46,0:06:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go. I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.61,0:06:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.09,0:06:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dancing was beautiful.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.97,0:06:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're making me blush.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.23,0:06:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.72,0:06:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just one in the crowd of dancers. \NI bet you couldn't even find me. {lit: see my face}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:20.19,0:06:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No, on the contrary. \NYou were the only one I saw.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.36,0:06:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.25,0:06:54.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, our happiness wasn't meant to last.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.64,0:06:58.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,I had a sudden stroke of bad luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.07,0:07:18.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,Some of the staff at the embassy \Nhad never liked me.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.74,0:07:23.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,They reported my behavior to the main office in Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.49,0:07:29.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,They claimed that my relationship with Elise was affecting my work.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.52,0:07:31.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,That was a slanderous\N distortion of the facts,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.97,0:07:34.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,but it was enough to incur \Nthe director's wrath.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.55,0:07:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If he returns to Japan immediately, \Nwe'll cover his return trip, at least.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.31,0:07:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we'll cut off\N all salary and support.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.63,0:07:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's too cruel to be true! \NI can't stand it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.98,0:07:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't live without you!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.91,0:07:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Toyotaro! Don't go back! \NDon't leave me!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.49,0:07:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.17,0:08:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not the kind of man \Nto give in to their blackmail.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.07,0:08:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't leave you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.37,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you, Toyotaro. \NI couldn't live without you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.67,0:08:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you too, Elise. \NI could never leave you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.31,0:08:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, I'll look for another job.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.94,0:08:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take any job, whatever it may be.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.89,0:08:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll have to find a new place to live.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.60,0:08:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You could stay at my house!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.52,0:08:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Your house?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.94,0:08:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless it's too small for you, please do.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.79,0:08:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,At least to save you rent money.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.06,0:08:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What about your mother?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.74,0:08:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right. \NI've already talked to her.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.87,0:08:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her we might be married soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.77,0:08:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Elise...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.55,0:08:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But it would be better for now
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.87,0:08:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,not to tell her you've lost your job.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.39,0:08:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She gets very unpredictable \Nwhen it comes to money.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.53,0:08:57.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so my new life began.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.54,0:09:01.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,Though, of course, I felt \Nan indescribable emptiness
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.11,0:09:03.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,at the thought of never seeing my homeland again.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.89,0:09:07.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'd be lying if I said that I felt no regrets.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.84,0:09:12.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,But for the time being, I was more preoccupied with how to make a living.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.33,0:09:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ota.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.92,0:09:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Aizawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.76,0:09:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My boy, I've been looking for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.24,0:09:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know you'd moved out \Nof your rented room.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.44,0:09:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.58,0:09:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go someplace we can talk in peace.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.94,0:09:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But I...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.64,0:09:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I may have work for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.41,0:09:47.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,That man was Aizawa Kenkichi, a foreign ministry secretary,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.85,0:09:50.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,who'd been dispatched to Berlin around the same time as I.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.52,0:09:53.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,He'd been a friend since college.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.37,0:09:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A correspondent for the {\i1}Tokyo Daily News{\i0}?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.57,0:09:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. They're a daily newspaper,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.76,0:10:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but the articles don't have to be highly specialized.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.05,0:10:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Politics, art, lifestyle... anything goes.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.17,0:10:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd write about the everyday happenings
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.54,0:10:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of your life in a column called "The Berlin Diaries."
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.54,0:10:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more than I'd ever hoped for!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.04,0:10:15.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,After learning of my dismissal,\N Aizawa talked
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.59,0:10:19.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,to his acquaintance,\N the editor of the {\i0}Tokyo Daily News.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:19.59,0:10:24.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was the first time I'd felt this immense gratitude for having such good friends.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.84,0:10:48.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,And that winter...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.07,0:11:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a cold from overwork. \NIt's not serious. However...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.35,0:11:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife also seems to be pregnant.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.21,0:11:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be better if she refrained from performing on stage for the time being.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.83,0:11:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pregnant?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.75,0:11:35.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,Although I should have been elated,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.06,0:11:38.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,in my heart of hearts, \NI couldn't bring myself to feel any joy.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.47,0:11:43.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,Did I really want to spend \Nthe rest of my life in this foreign land?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.05,0:11:46.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I was going to be a father now.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.79,0:11:50.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,I loved Elise, \Nand that was the result of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.50,0:12:04.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was from Aizawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.03,0:12:08.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,Minister Amakata, for whom he worked as a secretary, was on his way to Berlin,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.86,0:12:11.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,and Aizawa absolutely wanted me to meet him.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.18,0:12:16.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,Aizawa thought it might be my only chance to redeem myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.21,0:12:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember to be polite.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.44,0:12:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you impress him, they might make you an incredibly good offer.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.84,0:12:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.48,0:12:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They might offer you a job. \NYou're such a talented interpreter!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.03,0:12:44.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,Just as Elise predicted, the minister\N hired me as his personal interpreter
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.74,0:12:47.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,for the duration of his stay.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.40,0:12:52.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,But when Aizawa invited me \Nto dinner one night,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.16,0:12:55.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,he delivered a fatal verdict to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.54,0:12:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You want me to leave Elise?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.46,0:13:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I know it's cruel,\N but your entire future hangs on this.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.80,0:13:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You still have a chance to put it right. {lit: take it back}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.63,0:13:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But that means...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.64,0:13:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Ota.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:09.63,0:13:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the perfect opportunity here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.66,0:13:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Minister Amakata is very impressed with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.42,0:13:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's prepared to offer you a major post\N if you'll return to Japan now.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.44,0:13:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't pass this up!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.28,0:13:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What you need to do now is to take the initiative
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.11,0:13:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and live up to the minister's expectations.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.64,0:13:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no shortage of education or talent, so why must you
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.44,0:13:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,remain forever entangled in your affection for this foreign woman?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.53,0:13:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand to see you wasting your life like this!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.97,0:13:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I'm not trying to say something bad about her.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.29,0:13:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if you really love her,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.63,0:13:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it was just the loneliness of living abroad that drove you to that.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.96,0:13:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to make up your mind once and for all!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.77,0:13:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sorry, you don't have to decide immediately.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.57,0:14:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Next week, the minister will be traveling to St. Petersburg in Russia.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.26,0:14:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, he'll want you along to interpret for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:06.08,0:14:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to make the call\N when you two return to Berlin.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.46,0:14:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.77,0:14:16.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,I understood Aizawa's\N concerns all too well.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.59,0:14:18.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,And I was glad to have him.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.80,0:14:21.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,But does he really think
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.07,0:14:24.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'd be able to leave my life\N with Elise behind so easily?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.84,0:14:26.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,No, how could I ever leave it behind?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.61,0:14:29.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,She was carrying my child.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.89,0:14:33.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't get Aizawa's words about this being
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.60,0:14:36.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,the watershed moment\N of my life out of my head.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.60,0:14:41.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,He may be right. This probably is my last chance to make up my mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.43,0:14:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Darling, I hope you're well.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.27,0:15:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only been ten days since you left Berlin,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.24,0:15:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but it already feels like many months have passed.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.27,0:15:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's because of the loneliness,\N but I've gotten a little sicker these days.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.78,0:15:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor says it's anemia.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.92,0:15:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying not to push myself,\N for the baby's sake,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.38,0:15:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and to look after myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.70,0:15:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been praying that everything goes well for you with the current job, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.85,0:15:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When I think that after this, they might want you to go back to Japan anyway...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.09,0:15:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel my heart sink.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.32,0:15:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're my husband.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.53,0:15:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You promised that you'd stay here in Berlin with me forever.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.73,0:15:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll always trust you.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.91,0:15:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, my beloved Toyotaro.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.59,0:15:50.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,They say some things in this world are able to foreshadow our future.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.52,0:15:52.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,Elise's letter must've been one of them.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.28,0:15:59.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'd promised to Aizawa to make\N a decision by the end of the trip.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.10,0:16:01.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't bring myself to do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.89,0:16:05.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,What should I do? \NI was at my wits' end.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.40,0:16:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Darling!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.28,0:16:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Elise.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.54,0:16:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home, darling!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.85,0:16:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back. We missed you. {stock phrase in japanese, idk what to put here}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.93,0:16:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.55,0:16:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.84,0:16:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You look a little emaciated. \NAre you feeling all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.73,0:16:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm fine. Just a little tired.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.92,0:16:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And how are you, Elise?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.97,0:16:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel much better,\N now that you're home again.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.94,0:16:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.75,0:16:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what these are?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.21,0:16:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.95,0:16:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're diapers.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.73,0:16:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Diapers?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.70,0:16:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It took me a while, \Nbut I sewed them all.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.80,0:17:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you proud of me?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:02.45,0:17:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope our child has dark eyes like yours. He'll be lovely!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.50,0:17:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's give him a Japanese name too!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.25,0:17:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ernsttaro. Or maybe Ernstjiro? {the guy's name is Ōta Toyotarō - not sure if she means to modify his japanese surname like that? or only use part of it? in any case, sounds retarded}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.23,0:17:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They both sound so lovely!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.94,0:17:19.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,And finally, the fateful day arrived.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.47,0:17:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't wait any longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.61,0:17:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The minister's leaving next week.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.90,0:17:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that you could return to Japan with him.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.31,0:17:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to make up your mind!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.43,0:17:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ota, as your friend, \NI'll say it one last time.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.19,0:17:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you pass this up, \Nyou'll never return to Japan again!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.79,0:17:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what you want? Well?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.97,0:18:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the minister...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.16,0:18:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to accept...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.12,0:18:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,his offer.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.31,0:18:16.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,My mind was in a blur as I walked away from the hotel.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.19,0:18:22.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,I didn't know what I was thinking, \Nor where I was going.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.14,0:18:26.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,But I did feel a stabbing pain in my heart,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.04,0:18:31.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,and an accusing voice ringing in my ears: "Traitor! Traitor!"
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.59,0:18:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.60,0:18:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Elise! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.68,0:18:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He's late. \NI hope nothing's happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.54,0:19:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Darling! What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.75,0:19:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on, darling! Toyotaro!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.73,0:19:21.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,I finally woke up five days later.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.69,0:19:25.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,I've been feverish and unconscious this whole time.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.21,0:19:30.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,But in those five days, \Na catastrophe had struck.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.24,0:19:43.72,Top,,0,0,0,,Go to sleep in your mother's arms...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.96,0:19:42.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,Poor girl. I'm afraid it's my fault that she ended up this way.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.83,0:19:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Ota.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.12,0:19:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard you were sick, \NI came right over.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.26,0:19:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to tell them everything that happened the night before.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.44,0:19:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lying! It just can't be true!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.89,0:19:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Toyotaro would never betray us!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.47,0:20:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd never abandon us!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.16,0:20:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotta be a lie!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.58,0:20:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's true,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.87,0:20:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'll kill him! \NAnd then I'll kill myself!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:15.97,0:20:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lie, isn't it, darling?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.66,0:20:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, tell me it's a lie!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.41,0:20:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.53,0:20:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lie!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.06,0:20:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she lost her senses.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.85,0:20:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor said she'd suffered an extreme mental shock.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.92,0:20:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was at least a saving grace \Nthat it happened while you were asleep.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.93,0:20:52.70,Top,,0,0,0,,Go to sleep, go to sleep...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.70,0:20:58.85,Top,,0,0,0,,Sleep in your mother's arms...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.68,0:21:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Elise...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.83,0:21:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need your medicine? \NI'll bring it for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.30,0:21:27.49,Top,,0,0,0,,Go to sleep... Go to sleep...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.49,0:21:33.57,Top,,0,0,0,,Sleep in your mother's arms...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.54,0:21:37.20,Top,,0,0,0,,Go to sleep...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.43,0:21:32.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Elise! This is all my fault!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.17,0:21:47.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,A few days later, I left Berlin and was on my way back to Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.16,0:21:51.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,Aizawa gave Elise's mother enough money
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.60,0:21:56.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,to support herself, Elise, \Nand my unborn child in my stead.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.64,0:21:57.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.25,0:22:00.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,That did nothing to lessen my crimes.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.66,0:22:07.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'd have to live with this burden \Nfor the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:09.06,0:22:14.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,In this harsh world, a friend like Aizawa Kenkichi is very rare indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.54,0:22:22.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yet a trace of hatred for him \Nstill lingers in my mind to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.79,0:22:38.42,Song,,0,0,0,,I write a letter to my loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.42,0:22:45.59,Song,,0,0,0,,I write and tear it, tear it, and write again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.59,0:22:52.18,Song,,0,0,0,,I throw the rolled up paper at the window {meaning at the glass, probably as a distraction}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.18,0:22:59.14,Song,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside, just like the tears on my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.40,0:23:07.24,Song,,0,0,0,,Life is a sea, youth is a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.24,0:23:14.29,Song,,0,0,0,,My love, please come and save me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.29,0:23:16.41,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.58,0:23:20.46,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.46,0:23:27.97,Song,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.97,0:23:37.47,Song,,0,0,0,,Not a single star in sight, in the sea of ​​sadness
